I"R<p>The original, almost hour-long episodes out of Radiolab are some of my very favorite science journalism. Flu-afflicted, I listened to the <a href="https://www.wnycstudios.org/story/shrink" target="_blank">Mimiviruses</a> episode during an otherwise insufferable traffic jam in Tel Aviv and it made me nervous that the cars would start moving again before I could finish it. My other two favorites are about <a href="https://www.wnycstudios.org/story/91684-stochasticity" target="_blank">chance</a> and <a href="https://www.wnycstudios.org/story/211119-colors" target="_blank">color</a>.</p>
